EASTMAN KODAK CO. v. NATIONAL PARK BANK et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. December 11, 1917.) No. 71. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Hubbell, Taylor, Goodwin & Moser, of Rochester, N. Y. (Walter S. Hubbell and Clarence P. Moser, both of Rochester, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Louis F. Doyle, C. H. Payne, Carter, Ledyard & Milburn, and Geller, Ralston & Horan, all of New York City (Edward H. Blanc and James F. Horan, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before WARD, ROGERS, and HOUGH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (231 Fed. 320) affirmed.-
